{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NdM2C2iFzTbYBbuR4KVcek","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Excellent! The node has:\n- 40 CPUs\n- ~157GB memory (~164908288 KiB)\n- Plenty of capacity\n\nCurrent allocations are minimal. So I can allocate 2-3Gi per ES node without issues.\n\nLet me now write the full deployment manifest. I'll put everything in a single file for easy application.\n\nKey decisions:\n1. StatefulSet named `es`, serviceName `es-internal`\n2. Headless service `es-internal` for pod discovery\n3. `es-http` ClusterIP service on port 9200\n4. ConfigMap `es-config` with elasticsearch.yml\n5. PDB `es-pdb` with maxUnavailable: 1\n6. PVCs via volumeClaimTemplates using `standard` storage class (10Gi each)\n7. For the init container, I can either use busybox or the ES image itself to handle permissions\n\nI'm considering whether I actually need an init container to fix data directory permissions, or if I can just rely on `securityContext.fsGroup` since the ES container runs as user 1000.\n\nWith `fsGroup: 1000` in the pod security context, Kubernetes will automatically chown the volume, so I can skip the init container. For the Elasticsearch 8.x configuration, I need to set the node name dynamically from the pod name via environment variables, configure discovery seed hosts using the headless service or pod FQDNs, and specify the initial master nodes as `[\"es-0\",\"es-1\",\"es-2\"]`. For transport TLS on port 9300, I'll use the existing certificate with `verification_mode: certificate` to verify without strict hostname checking, which should work fine since each node connects to others using their pod hostnames. For node roles, the default setup where each node has all roles works fine for a 3-node cluster. For discovery, I can use the headless service DNS name `[\"es-internal\"]` which will resolve to all pod IPs, and ES will retry connections as pods come online during startup.\n\nHowever, there's a timing issue: the headless service only returns IPs of Ready pods, so newly starting pods won't appear in DNS yet. I should enable `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service so that pods can discover each other even before they're fully ready.\n\nFor the initial cluster bootstrap in ES 8.x, I need to set `cluster.initial_master_nodes` with the node names that match the pod names (`es-0`, `es-1`, `es-2`). Once the cluster forms, this setting isn't needed for restarts since ES uses the stored cluster state.\n\nI also need to handle the `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` environment variable to set the password for the elastic user during initialization. Writing Kubernetes manifest... I need to fix the YAML syntax by removing quotes from boolean values and converting the certificate authorities to list format, then set up the security context for the StatefulSet to run as the elasticsearch user.\n\nConfiguring the security context...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":478,"cache_read_input_tokens":32315,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":478},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e75b3fab-749e-4aeb-968c-fec95891c9a6","uuid":"6cbd3205-6558-4b04-884a-5641ceacbd32","request_id":"req_011Cc8tRTgxHdQY124M9bovJ"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NdM2C2iFzTbYBbuR4KVcek","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Plenty of resources available. I'll now write the full deployment manifest — ConfigMap, headless service, `es-http` service, PDB, and StatefulSet."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":478,"cache_read_input_tokens":32315,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":478},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e75b3fab-749e-4aeb-968c-fec95891c9a6","uuid":"e6404a30-a1e8-4d86-b886-67e52c1e8fb9","request_id":"req_011Cc8tRTgxHdQY124M9bovJ"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NdM2C2iFzTbYBbuR4KVcek","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014zo6sKvnAgsAB2Jw9bU9rD","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mydata/karma/runs/long-examples/elasticsearch-long-transform-scale-upgrade-20260617_130909/stages/stage_01/es-cluster.yaml","content":"---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ConfigMap\nmetadata:\n  name: es-config\n  namespace: elasticsearch\ndata:\n  elasticsearch.yml: |\n    cluster.name: elasticsearch\n    node.name: ${POD_NAME}\n    network.host: 0.0.0.0\n    http.port: 9200\n    transport.port: 9300\n    discovery.seed_hosts: [\"es-internal\"]\n    cluster.initial_master_nodes: [\"es-0\",\"es-1\",\"es-2\"]\n    xpack.security.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.http.ssl.certificate_authorities: [\"/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\"]\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: true\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.key: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.key\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/tls.crt\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.certificate_authorities: [\"/usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs/ca.crt\"]\n    xpack.security.transport.ssl.verification_mode: certificate\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-internal\n  namespace: elasticsearch\n  labels:\n    app: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  clusterIP: None\n  publishNotReadyAddresses: true\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n  - name: transport\n    port: 9300\n    protocol: TCP\n  - name: http\n    port: 9200\n    protocol: TCP\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Service\nmetadata:\n  name: es-http\n  namespace: elasticsearch\n  labels:\n    app: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  type: ClusterIP\n  selector:\n    app: elasticsearch\n  ports:\n  - name: https\n    port: 9200\n    targetPort: 9200\n    protocol: TCP\n---\napiVersion: policy/v1\nkind: PodDisruptionBudget\nmetadata:\n  name: es-pdb\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  maxUnavailable: 1\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n---\napiVersion: apps/v1\nkind: StatefulSet\nmetadata:\n  name: es\n  namespace: elasticsearch\nspec:\n  serviceName: es-internal\n  replicas: 3\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: elasticsearch\n  template:\n    metadata:\n      labels:\n        app: elasticsearch\n    spec:\n      securityContext:\n        fsGroup: 1000\n        runAsUser: 1000\n        runAsGroup: 1000\n      initContainers:\n      - name: sysctl\n        image: docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1\n        command: [\"sh\", \"-c\", \"sysctl -w vm.max_map_count=262144 || true\"]\n        securityContext:\n          privileged: true\n          runAsUser: 0\n      containers:\n      - name: elasticsearch\n        image: docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1\n        env:\n        - name: POD_NAME\n          valueFrom:\n            fieldRef:\n              fieldPath: metadata.name\n        - name: ELASTIC_PASSWORD\n          valueFrom:\n            secretKeyRef:\n              name: elastic-password\n              key: password\n        - name: ES_JAVA_OPTS\n          value: \"-Xms2g -Xmx2g\"\n        ports:\n        - containerPort: 9200\n          name: http\n          protocol: TCP\n        - containerPort: 9300\n          name: transport\n          protocol: TCP\n        resources:\n          requests:\n            memory: \"2Gi\"\n            cpu: \"500m\"\n          limits:\n            memory: \"4Gi\"\n            cpu: \"2\"\n        volumeMounts:\n        - name: config\n          mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/elasticsearch.yml\n          subPath: elasticsearch.yml\n        - name: certs\n          mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/config/certs\n          readOnly: true\n        - name: data\n          mountPath: /usr/share/elasticsearch/data\n        readinessProbe:\n          exec:\n            command:\n            - sh\n            - -c\n            - |\n              curl -sk -u \"elastic:${ELASTIC_PASSWORD}\" \\\n                https://localhost:9200/_cluster/health \\\n                | grep -qE '\"status\":\"(green|yellow)\"'\n          initialDelaySeconds: 60\n          periodSeconds: 10\n          timeoutSeconds: 10\n          failureThreshold: 6\n        livenessProbe:\n          tcpSocket:\n            port: 9300\n          initialDelaySeconds: 60\n          periodSeconds: 20\n          timeoutSeconds: 5\n          failureThreshold: 6\n      volumes:\n      - name: config\n        configMap:\n          name: es-config\n      - name: certs\n        secret:\n          secretName: es-http-tls\n  volumeClaimTemplates:\n  - metadata:\n      name: data\n    spec:\n      accessModes: [\"ReadWriteOnce\"]\n      storageClassName: standard\n      resources:\n        requests:\n          storage: 10Gi\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":478,"cache_read_input_tokens":32315,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":478},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e75b3fab-749e-4aeb-968c-fec95891c9a6","uuid":"e62ed590-40ee-4ce5-a62d-ae20bd923b83","request_id":"req_011Cc8tRTgxHdQY124M9bovJ"}
