{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0164YTBe9eeCP5qieL9Spnsv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is working. Here's a summary of what was deployed:\n\n**Resources created in `elasticsearch` namespace:**\n\n| Resource | Name | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| ConfigMap | `es-config` | `elasticsearch.yml` with TLS, discovery, and security settings |\n| Service (headless) | `es-internal` | Pod-to-pod transport discovery (`publishNotReadyAddresses: true`) |\n| Service (ClusterIP) | `es-http` | Client access on port 9200 |\n| PodDisruptionBudget | `es-pdb` | `maxUnavailable: 1` |\n| StatefulSet | `es` | 3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` |\n| PVCs | `data-es-{0,1,2}` | 10Gi each via `standard` storage class |\n\n**Key design decisions:**\n- `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` — all 3 pods start simultaneously so they can form a quorum; sequential startup would deadlock (es-0 needs peers to elect a master before becoming Ready)\n- `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service — lets nodes discover each other before readiness probes pass\n- Same `es-http-tls` cert used for both HTTP and transport TLS with `verification_mode: certificate` (skips hostname check, validates cert chain only)\n- `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` injected from the existing `elastic-password` secret\n\n**Verification:**\n- Cluster status: **green**, 3/3 nodes\n- Write to `test-index/_doc/1`: **created**\n- Read back: **found** with correct source"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":408,"cache_read_input_tokens":43805,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":408},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e75b3fab-749e-4aeb-968c-fec95891c9a6","uuid":"9fb8031d-702e-44b1-9886-20e41e0bb422","re